fear or are just unfamiliar with the main lines of the Four Knights. Their
mistaken belief is that they will throw us off simply by not cooperating,
through the refusal to bring that last knight out. We need to be ready for
this by booking up on the various dodges. In this chapter we cover: a) 3...Bc5;
b) 3...Bb4; c) 3...g6; d) 3...Be7; and e) 3...f5. --- Here is the good news:
Of these various dodge attempts, a) and b) fail to equalize, c) and d) tend to
be passive but solid, and e) is downright awful for Black.} *

